Comparison of radiographic findings between intubation and non-intubation groups in patients of MERS pneumonia is summarized in Table 2
. Peak radiographic score was significantly higher in intubation group, compared with non-intubation group (p = 0.006). It also revealed significantly higher diffuse lung involvement in intubation group, while peripheral lung involvement was more common in non-intubation group (p = 0.003). Additionally, all patients of intubation group demonstrated fibrosing sequelae on serial CXRs, whereas only 33% of the patients in non-intubation group showed remaining opacity (p = 0.005) (Fig. 2
).
